Definition of suicide: the act or an instance of taking one's own life voluntarily and intentionally


Suicide rate in the US increased 24% from 1999 to 2014, for both males and females ages 10-74, rising from 10.5 to 13.0 per 100,000 population.

It is the 10th leading cause of death in the US for all ages, taking 41, 149 lives in 2013.
It is the 2nd leading cause of death worldwide for those aged 15-24. 

The most frequent suicide method for males was use of firearms (55.4%) while for women, the most frequent method was females (34.1%). The suicide rate for males is more than triple that for females, while females attempt suicide three times as often as males.


